Imposter syndrome ✨ I have never talked about it but experienced it so so many times and I am sure you have too 🥲 

So what is it? 🤨
It is the feeling of self-doubt and personal incompetence that persist despite your education, experience, and accomplishments 😔
“What am I doing here?” “I do not belong here” “Everyone must be so much better than me” “I am not worthy of the job”

I never knew something like this existed and found out after I quit my first engineering job.
So why am I talking about this?
Because you might feel the same and it is completely normal 🙂

Imposter feelings represent a conflict between your own self-perception and the way others perceive you. To counter these feelings, you might end up working harder and holding yourself to ever higher standards. This pressure can eventually take a toll on your emotional well-being and your performance.

My advice on overcoming it: If your colleagues and your team/company is happy with your results and work, just calm down a little. Believe in yourself and your abilities! Stop comparing yourself to others. You will eventually feel better over time as you get used to your colleagues and the environment you work in. 

Have you ever experienced it? Share your thoughts or advice in the comment section below ⬇️ ✍️ (I am sure you can help someone) 🥰

On the contrary, Apple never officially upgraded from MVC and their project samples are bad in terms of code quality. Luckily, the worldwide dev community compensates for that with articles and guidelines.
•
🪞 𝙇𝙤𝙩𝙨 𝙤𝙛 𝙨𝙞𝙢𝙞𝙡𝙖𝙧𝙞𝙩𝙞𝙚𝙨 - the languages (Swift and Kotlin) are very much alike, the navigation between screens is similar, the UI is now similar with SwiftUI and Compose, the concept of flavors and targets is quite alike, etc. You'll quickly get up to speed.

A structure is a user-defined data type in C/C++. A structure creates a data type that can be used to group items of possibly different types into a single type. 

In C++, a structure is the same as a class except for a few differences. The most important of them is security. A Structure is not secure and cannot hide its implementation details from the end user while a class is secure and can hide its programming and designing details.

JavaScript Frameworks Battles,🤺 (Part.4)⁣⁣
⁣
-) Svelte ⁣
⁣
Svelte is a modern JavaScript framework for building static web apps that are quick, lean, and enjoyable to use for developers. Svelte may be used to create single, reusable components for any project, including bigger apps developed in Angular, React, Vue, or any other framework.⁣
⁣
Pros ➕ ➕⁣
-) Components Easy to Understand⁣
-) Concise Code and Light Files ⁣
-) Responsiveness with Labeled Statements⁣
-) Simple Out-Of-The-Box Global State Management⁣
-) Built-in Accessibility and Unused CSS Checks⁣
⁣
Cons ❌ ❌⁣
-) It doesn’t offer any of the features of those frameworks (React or Vue)⁣
-) Vanilla.js first in order to have a better understanding of Svelte⁣
-) Not suitable for larger teams that want to build every extra feature⁣
⁣
However ... is Svelte getting more and more popular? 🤔⁣

Yes, because of ...⁣
... very small size once compiled⁣
... its source code is easy to understand ⁣
... Svelte.js doesn’t embed a virtual DOM⁣
... the final script is very light and fast to run⁣
... you can use HTML markup or XML files⁣
⁣
In their words ... 
… simple, powerful, and elegant 💬⁣
⁣
